spread out data set around the mean value.

102
00:07:04.843 --> 00:07:07.423
While lower standard deviation and

103
00:07:07.423 --> 00:07:12.504
variance result in a more tightly
dispersed data set around the mean.

104
00:07:12.504 --> 00:07:14.976
Let's discuss our specific example.

105
00:07:14.976 --> 00:07:19.786
It will be simple and explore the use
of regression analysis to predict

106
00:07:19.786 --> 00:07:25.019
visits to a website based on the number
of social media mentions of the site.

107
00:07:25.019 --> 00:07:29.115
Our thesis here is that it's
reasonable to think that as mentions

108
00:07:29.115 --> 00:07:31.578
of a website on social media increase, 

109
00:07:31.578 --> 00:07:35.409
the number of people who visit
the site will also increase, and

110
00:07:35.409 --> 00:07:39.870
result in increased web traffic or
page hits to the site.

111
00:07:39.870 --> 00:07:43.970
Starting with a thesis like this is
fundamental to regression analysis.

112
00:07:45.180 --> 00:07:48.040
This statistical method can
be used to determine if

113
00:07:48.040 --> 00:07:51.430
there is a correlative relationship
between two variables.

114
00:07:51.430 --> 00:07:56.140
In our case, the relationship between
the number of social media mentions,

115
00:07:56.140 --> 00:08:00.000
the independent variable, and
visits to our website,

116
00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:01.650
the dependent variable.

117
00:08:01.650 --> 00:08:06.310
We have measures of the strength of this
relationship which we will discuss later.

118
00:08:06.310 --> 00:08:10.320
If these measures indicate a strong
relationship we can conclude

119
00:08:10.320 --> 00:08:15.320
that social media mentions and
visits to our website are related.

120
00:08:15.320 --> 00:08:19.630
A strong relationship determined via
linear regression analysis does not,

121
00:08:19.630 --> 00:08:25.220
however imply a causal relationship
between the two variables.

122
00:08:25.220 --> 00:08:28.790
Said differently,
it does not imply that traffic

123
00:08:28.790 --> 00:08:33.510
increased to our website because
of social media mentions,

124
00:08:33.510 --> 00:08:38.070
but, rather,
that increased web traffic to our website

125
00:08:38.070 --> 00:08:42.380
tends to increase with increases
in social media mentions.

126
00:08:42.380 --> 00:08:44.400
This is an important distinction,

127
00:08:44.400 --> 00:08:48.260
though causal analysis is beyond
the scope of this module.

